lila-codex
==========

This crate is a fork of `codex-client-sdk` (crates.io version 0.107.0), originally from:

    https://github.com/tosimpletech/agent-client-sdk-package

The original work is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (see LICENSE).
The original crate's lib name `codex` is preserved so consumers keep `use codex::...`.

It is vendored into lila-rs and is NOT published to crates.io. lila carries it as a fork
because the published SDK lags the codex CLI's JSONL protocol and hard-fails on output that
newer CLIs emit.

Modifications by the lila-rs authors
------------------------------------

- Added the `in_progress` variant to `PatchApplyStatus` (src/items.rs). The codex CLI
  (≥ ~0.141) emits this for in-flight file patches; the unpatched 0.107 SDK fails every
  worker run with `unknown variant 'in_progress'`.

- Forward-compatibility hardening (src/items.rs, src/events.rs): added a `#[serde(other)]`
  catch-all variant (`Unknown`) to the protocol enums that mirror CLI output —
  `CommandExecutionStatus`, `PatchChangeKind`, `PatchApplyStatus`, `McpToolCallStatus`,
  `ThreadItem`, and `ThreadEvent`. An unrecognized value from a newer CLI now deserializes
  into `Unknown` instead of failing the whole event stream; lila treats it as a no-op. This
  is the structural fix for the recurring `unknown variant` class of breakage.
